    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're designing a music app that creates personalized playlists. To get started, the app needs to remember the user's favorite artist.\r\n\r\n1. Create a variable called `favorite_artist`.\r\n\r\n2. Assign it a string value like `\"Beyonce\"`\r\n\r\n   *Remember to put quotes around text when you're assigning a string value — Python needs to know it's text, not code!*\r\n\r\n3. Use `print()` to display a message like\r\n\r\n   ```\r\n   Now playing top hits from Beyonce.\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nYou can use **commas** in a `print()` statement to combine text and variables. For example:\r\n\r\n```\r\nprint(\"Name:\", first_name)\r\n```",
